  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you see phone numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp:\n\n1. Contacts not saved\n- The phone number might not be saved in your phone's contact list\n- WhatsApp uses saved contacts to display names\n\n2. Sync issues\n- WhatsApp contact sync might be disabled\n- Your contact list may not be updated\n\n3. Settings problem\n- Check WhatsApp contact display settings\n- Verify phone contacts synchronization\n\nSolutions:\n1. Save phone numbers to your contacts\n2. Check WhatsApp settings:\n- Settings > Contacts > \"Show contact names\"\n3. Sync contacts:\n- On iPhone: Settings > WhatsApp > Contacts\n- On Android: WhatsApp > Settings > Contacts\n4. Restart WhatsApp\n5. Restart your phone\n\nIf issues persist, try:\n- Reinstalling WhatsApp\n- Checking phone's contact sync settings\n- Ensuring latest WhatsApp version\n\nWould you like me to provide more detailed steps for your specific device?",
